HEADWORD: Symphyseotomy
<hw>Sym`phy*se*ot"o*my</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL.
<ets>symphysis pubis</ets> + Gr. <?/ to cut.]</ety> <fld>(Surg.)</fld>
<def>The operation of dividing the symphysis pubis for the purpose of
facilitating labor; -- formerly called the <xex>Sigualtian
section</xex>.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>symphysotomy</asp>.]</altsp> <rj><au>Dunglison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

